cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with adapting a convolutional neural network (CNN) based object counter to additional visual domains and object types while still preserving the original counting function. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses the use of domain-specific normalization and scaling operators, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a singular patch-based counting regressor, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a new cell counting dataset, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
